.TH GIT\-ISSUE\-STATUS 1 "2026-03-01" "git-issue 1.0.0-rc1" "Git Issue Tracker"
.SH NAME
git\-issue\-status \- print an issue status report
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git\-issue\-status
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prints a summary of all issues: counts by status and by priority,
followed by a list of open issues sorted by priority.
.PP
Reads issue data directly from git refs using plumbing commands.
.SH OUTPUT
.nf
Issue Status Report
Generated: 2026-03-01 12:00:00

Summary:
Total Issues: 26

By Status:
  Open: 5
  In Progress: 3
  Closed: 15
  Blocked: 3

By Priority:
  High/Critical: 4
  Medium: 18
  Low: 4

Open Issues by Priority:
  ...
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1)
